    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1863-11-02T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1863-11-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="189"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d189">
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Immediate.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Her Majesty’s Treasury</persName> to <persName type="to"
                        >Laird Brothers</persName>.</head>
                <note rend="inline" type="source">15, 5862/11.</note>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Treasury Chambers,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1863-11-02">
                            <hi rend="italic">November</hi> 2, 1863.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Gentlemen:</hi> In reply to your letter of the 30th ultimo,
                    representing the danger which the iron-clad vessels now under seizure will incur
                    in consequence of their being removed from your premises, I am commanded by the
                    lords commissioners of her Majesty’s treasury to acquaint you that their
                    lordships, having been in communication with the secretary of state in reference
                    to your letter, have nothing to add to the communication made to you by telegram
                    on the 29th ultimo.</p>
                <p>I am, gentlemen, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>GEO. A. HAMILTON.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Messrs. <hi rend="smallcaps">Laird,</hi>
                        <hi rend="italic">Birkenhead.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
